{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:34:37.900Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Verifying Data Sanitization**\n\nI've just confirmed the `/api/v1/users` route successfully strips the `passwordHash` field from user entries, addressing the sensitive data issue in list endpoints. I've also verified that this is the only sensitive field, so this satisfies the requirement to avoid leaking sensitive information. Now I'm checking other routes that might return user information, starting with `/api/v1/auth/me/route.ts`.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:34:39.386Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Confirming Security Checks**\n\nI'm now verifying the RBAC boundary logic within each endpoint. I've confirmed password hashes are stripped in the `[id]` route too, as well as the `/api/v1/users` route. I'm actively inspecting the project list endpoint, and will inspect RBAC filters to see where boundaries are enforced server-side. I've begun to review `/api/v1/projects/route.ts`.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
