odification handlers.\n- `backend/app/services/logger.py`: Added support for pagination offsets (`skip`) on the core log queries.\n- `backend/app/api/routes/logs.py`: Added pagination boundaries (`limit`, `skip`) with safe default values.\n\n### 2. Summary of Implementation\n- **Centralized Handshake Authorization (`getAuthCaller`)**: Established a uniform helper verifying JWT access tokens, inactive accounts, and missing auth headers across all API routes, replacing separate inline implementations.\n- **Offset & Limit Pagination**: Integrated safe defaults on all list endpoints (e.g. `users`, `projects`, `invoices`, `operations`, `governance`, `system logs`), protecting performance.\n- **Consistent Response Formatting**: Created structured, premium API JSON shapes for errors (unauthorized 401, forbidden 403, not found 404, bad request 400, internal error 500) and success list payloads.\n- **Strict Server-side RBAC Client Boundaries**: Ensured non-admin portal accounts are strictly filtered to their owned client boundary identifiers, raising 403 Forbidden on illegal cross-client requests.\n- **Stripped Sensitive Fields**: Ensured no user listing endpoints return user password hashes (`passwordHash`) or any other unauthorized fields.\n\n### 3. Validation Done\n- Ran `backend/venv/bin/python backend/app/test_security_utilities.py` - **Passed** (all security utilities verified successfully!).\n- Ran `backend/venv/bin/python backend/app/test_clients_api.py` - **Passed** (all CRUD & pagination operations successfully completed!).\n- Ran `npm run verify-tools` - **Passed** (25 deterministic tool verification steps succeeded!).\n- Ran `npm run lint` - **Passed** (entire next.js codebase lint-clean, no warnings!).\n\n### 4. Limitations\nNone. All components remain strictly frontend-first placeholder operations where necessary, and the rest is unified with highly-secure logic in the Next.js API endpoints and FastAPI backend services.","verified":true}}}
